snippet.textDisplay: He is adorable! So happy he’s doing so well Colleen - truly you deserve the best! I don’t want to be a non-parent giving advice but this is more just me remembering being terrified, shy and anxious as a baby and as a young kid, I had a hard time making friends and i even had OCD, didn’t like being dirty so I would lay quietly in the office instead of everyone fighting to make me go outside... i even memorized the way the ppl in the office would answer the phone my age 3/4. I ended up loving cars as well because you can play for hours on your own. I was always a reader and stayed on my own except sports! Loved Swimming, Hockey & Badminton. Turns out a lot of the issues I had was because I was raised as an only child and honestly you learn how to enjoy your own company and you live through your smarts, and books and fantasy and imagination. I just wanted to tell you, sorry if I overstepped or anything ... I just really wanted to point out some similarities but at the end of the day you know him best and I promise no advice just similarities I noticed and I will tell that I also ended up being very social in middle school and high school so I did get there eventually but I took my time and observed it from afar first. I personally am happy being raised the way I was and I truly love the fact that my dad is my homie, ride or die style, and my mom is my best friend. I was and always will be closer to my family, our extended family is our immediate family but we are a lot of us when we get together. I’m pretty sure that’s why I gravitated to your channel and to all of your family members channels as well. It reminds my of my own family, playing games that can take hours, having some kids who love reading quietly on the side like Bailey but who really love to be musical. We have the Parker who has to show you his latest masterpiece of choreography, dance ninja awesomeness. I personally relate best to Rachel for sports, to you & Christopher for writing, dreaming big and enjoying weird humour because it’s the best kind, I also think I’m like Bailey and Flynn because of their quiet humble nature and their love of books and I see someone in my family through so many of yours so thank you for that because I’ve been ill and I can’t see them as often as I like. ❤️🤘🏽 Rock on Colleen!! (Thank you for getting me through some really tough times)
